Former speaker house of representatives, Ghali Umar Na’abba is alive, well and healthy, a family source has confirmed. Report on the rumoured death of the Kano born politician went viral on social media on Friday morning. Hussain Na’abba, a younger sister to ex-speaker considered untrue and outright fake. Ghali was the speaker of the house of representatives during the tenure of President Olusegun Obasanjo and active member of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). Ghali left former president Goodluck Jonathan camp and decamped from the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the heat of 2011 presidential campaign. In a telephone conversation with The Guardia, Hussaina said “The former speaker and my brother is alive and is very well. The rumour is just rumour and fake. “Alhaji is in London as we speak. He was held down in the wake of the COVID-19 Pandemic lockdown in London. He would return home Insha Allah the moment the road is clear. I spoke with him this morning the moment I saw the fake new,” Hussaina said. Meanwhile, the vice-chancellor, Kano University of Science and Technology, Wudil, Professor Musa Alhaji has announced the death of Arc. Dr Ghali Kabir Umar, of the Department of Architecture KUST Wudil. The death of Arc. Ghali Umar was being misconstrued for the former speaker.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .